<p><sup>Votes don't help the author, so I've vowed to always leave a comment with mine, at the very least whenever I rate an article negatively. If you feel the same, help out by leaving critique with more of your votes. Comment follows:</sup></p>
<p>The idea of Boweism as a pseudo-religion is a very interesting one, for me at least, but it's not enough to carry the article. The speech acts as a single-sided dialogue explaining everything that the previous article glossed over, but it's not much more than that. It's a lore dump: not a problem in and of itself, if it's necessary for the plot, but I wish this information could be presented a little more naturally, and it's the same information being presented twice (though more clearly this time). But beyond a nebulous goal of uniting a bunch of GoIs against the Foundation (which appears to have already been done, given the guests on-stage), I'm not too sure where we're going from here.</p>

